[[File:David Liljemark.jpg|thumb|David Liljemark]]
'''David "Dayw" Liljemark''' (born in 1973 in [[Karlstad]], [[Värmland County]]) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[list of comic creators|comic creator]], artist, and musician. Debuting at a young age in the Swedish [[fanzine]]/ [[mini-comic]] circles, Liljemark later became one of the most productive professional [[cartoonists]] of Sweden, having been published in big newspapers such as [[Dagens Nyheter]], magazines such as ''[[Galago (comics)|Galago]]'' and the Swedish edition of [[Mad Magazine]], and [[comic books]] such as ''[[Pyton|Mega-Pyton]]''.<ref name=svd>[http://www.svd.se/kultur/vulgart-och-groteskt-blir-mjukt-i-serieforpackning_98271.svd Vulgärt och groteskt blir mjukt i serieförpackning], ''[[Svenska Dagbladet]]'' 26 June 2013, retrieved 20 July 2014 {{sv icon}}</ref> He has also produced several [[comic album]]s.<ref name=dn>[http://www.dn.se/dnbok/karismatisk-kvacksalvare-blir-seriefigur/ Karismatisk kvacksalvare blir seriefigur] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924053149/http://www.dn.se/dnbok/karismatisk-kvacksalvare-blir-seriefigur/ |date=2015-09-24 }}, ''[[Dagens Nyheter]]'' 29 July 2009, retrieved 20 July 2014 {{sv icon}}</ref>

David Liljemark is also a musician, active in the Swedish band ''The Wonder Boys''.

Liljemark received the [[Gustaf Fröding]] stipend awarded by [[Karlstad Municipality]] in 2010.<ref>[http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=93&artikel=4214447 Tre delar på Frödingstipendium], ''[[Sveriges Radio]]'' 1 December 2010, retrieved 20 July 2014 {{sv icon}}</ref>

